<br>
If 90% of the guilds make a schedule and stick to it, the 10% of guilds who don't believe, care, or aren't concerned with that schedule will come and go as they please - and it will degenerate into FFA.<br>
<br>
The reality, however, is much more swayed the other way.  First of all, this server, lacking a scheduling system, has been FFA since the day it came up.  ...and get this, unlike the systems that many of us came from, it works.<br>
<br>
It's still possible to schedule things which a small number of groups have the resources for.  While the number grows every week, there are still probably few enough guilds with the strategy and numbers to kill <insert-big-target-here>.<br>
<br>
Those guilds can work out any rotation they want because it's possible to reach 100% agreement.  Or, if a single member of those guilds decide no schedule, they are FORCED to work in a similar fashion.<br>
<br>
The added burden is you can ~always~ enforce FFA.    You can ~never~ enforce a schedule.  The "rules" of the game support it.  Even in situations where GMs have asked other guilds to leave raids, it's because they made a determination that the <large-target> was "engaged" and supported the group that got to it first.  [We acknowledge things like clearing the fire giants and sitting in the prep-room to be "engaging" Nagafen, for example.]<br>
<br>
If you are in Nagafen's prep room buffing to kill the 'leezard, and another guild who just walks into Sol.B petitions that they scheduled to kill the dragon on leezard-schedule.com, guess who's gonna get to kill the dragon.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
...and to answer Faydin's question: "Say you are in your corner and they pull all the spawns. Why would you stay[?]"<br>
<br>
If we went to [plane] and set up camp, and a vastly superior force were there, one able to beat us to all - or nearly all of the spawns, we would leave.  I think I've made that clear.  FFA sometimes means you get 40 people, jump into the [plane entrance] and find 100 other people there.  On those days you go somewhere else.<br>
<br>
[We would of course have known 100 people were there, but guilds go /ANON so they don't get tells from other guilds asking when the portal is clear - so they can stay alone for as possible. -- But that's another rant.] <p><img src=http://www.goodnet.com/~matts/sig.bmp > </p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ff0000>- </font><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero>AyonaeRo</a><font color=#ff0000> - </font><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8>Raid Forum</a> <font color=#ff0000> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.5.6<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

